                 longer hind-limb bones) of this hypothesized adaptive allele
                 include functional characteristics that facilitate high levels
                 of voluntary wheel running (e.g., doubling of mass-specific
                 muscle aerobic capacity, increased fatigue resistance of
                 isolated muscles, longer hind-limb bones). Previously, we
                 created a backcross population suitable for mapping the
                 responsible locus. We phenotypically characterized the
                 population and mapped the Minimsc locus to a 2.6-Mb interval
